fields.title: Stumpz; the indoor cricket game
fields.history_note: This may have been a pre-1940 design and game produced in the 1950 s and 1960s as well.
fields.production_note: Thomas de la Rue & Co ltd, 10 Bunhill Row, London, EC1
fields.historical_context_note:
Rewards: runs gained
Forfeits: batmen out
No. of Players: any
Equipment required: see list under rules

Rules:
playing surface, green stiffened cloth printed in black to show a cricket pitch
Break Indicator, card printed to show a semicircle with 4 segments; metal arrow; Instructions for Bowler on the back
Stumpz Scoreboard, card printed to show 4 numbered circles each with a metal arrow
spinner, teetotum, black plastic marked Out or Not Out
Instructions for Batsman, printed with rules
*cards printed in green with a design on the reverse sides
     6 numbered 0 with CATCH at the top and bottom
     6 numbered 1 with CATCH  at the top and bottom
     9 numbered 1
     5 numbered 2 with CATCH at the top and bottom
     7 numbered 2
     4 numbered 3 with CATCH at the top and bottom
     4 numbered 3
     12 numbered 4
     2 numbered 6
*cards with plain green backs
     26 marked GOOD LENGTH
     13 marked HALF VOLLEY
     6  marked LONG HOP
     6 marked FULL TOSS
     2 marked YORKER
     1 marked NO-BALL
     1 marked WIDE
11 woodn cone shaped counters
booklet of rules
box.
